			"body": "As shown in the image, Joplin is currently in the pre-release version 3.6.4, and the window is in viewer mode. I selected some text and then opened the macOS global menu, “Copy” is greyed out, so I can’t copy via the global menu or use the cmd+C shortcut. The only way to copy is to right click on the selected text and choose “Copy” from the context menu. However, not being able to copy using the shortcut key is a significant obstacle.\r\n\r\nIn addition, I believe that “Select All” should not be greyed out either. This PR does not include a fix for this issue, but if you think it needs to be addressed, I can add a fix for it.\r\n\r\n![Xnip2026-03-14_15-28-18](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/12cdacbf-a8bc-4e1b-9133-3ec7b55c2a9e)\r\n",
